Well, if we go hypothetical, here would be my suggestion.<br>
<br>
Name - Fiery Protector, or Warsword of the Crusader<br>
Particle - Nice blade with Blue flames, or nature defender type look with shields or angels floating around Hilt, ala Sk epic.<br>
Stats - up HP/mana on the sword for stats, others are ok<br>
Ratio - Something like 45 40  (or a 40 40 with Bane Undead +20 on the blade, making it a 60 40 for undead only.  Possibly add +5 &lt;insert resist&gt; damage.  so the damage bonus is a bit higher if the mob isn't resistant.)<br>
Effect - Avatar Infusion (Mini avatar)   3 minute duration, half of the effects of the Avatar spell<br>
<br>
As for quest or just upgrade?   I wouldn't expect them to upgrade it outright.  Would have to be a new quest.<br>
<br>
<br>
Here is the thing though.   It cannot have a single component necessary from 1 named mob.   It must be a rare drop from a &quot;class&quot; of monsters.  <br>
<br>
I.e. Umbrous toilers drop the item rarely.   Or Raldukan's in Umbral.  Something like that.<br>
<br>
Personally, if they did it, the ideal way to do it would be, each quest piece can be farmed by 1 single group.   There is no 24 hour camp for named mob such and such who pops once per week.   Get a group, go kill in a zone, until you get the drop.    Make all components No Drop.<br>
<br>
Due to a lot of the zones in Luclin being a Single group raid.  I would use a lot of those zones.    Don't need a raid to go there, just need a group of capable friends.<br>
<br>
If they did that, each paladin can take the time to get the epic with friends, and there would be no fights over the specific spawns.   Everyone would have achance to do it, but the time involved is simply killing the right mobs in the right zone until you get it.   And while doing so, you would be getting other good items for your friends.<br>
<br>
just my opinion.<br>
<br>
wyrmbane<br>
<br>
