<br>
Name: Fiery Protector (nobrainer! =P)<br>
<br>
Graphic: An ornate hilt with a blade that looks like the standard rusty 2h blade, but a bright silver color, with maybe a slight taper to the blade with it broader at the hilt and slimming some at the top (but only a little!), and use the flame graphic from the original soulfire (looks MUCH better than the particle effect, and everyone can see it).<br>
<br>
How to obtain: An additional quest, definitely. Something without a big bottleneck, as we already have it, something that doesn't require ultra rare spawns. A triggered spawn would be good.<br>
<br>
Stats: Tough one. Can't make it "too good", but if it is only marginally upgraded there isn't much point. I would go with 51 dmg 46 dly (at the cuttoff for lowest delay with the 40 DB at 60), which would make it worse than GSoD and Lance of Thunder ratio-wise, but better than a lot of other stuff out there that is more easily available. 20-40 ac, +20 str sta wis, maybe some dex/agi, not important though, 10-20 to all resists, 100-125 hp and mana, and keep the proc the same, maybe upping the dd part slightly. If damage is "too good", lower dmg by 1-3 points and give it that much bane damage to undead.<br>
